5. Business Rules Engine (Hard Rules)
5.1 Source Precedence (Enrichment)

Rule ID: SRC-PREC-001 Rule: When populating a product field (e.g., description, image, barcode), the system MUST check sources in this order and stop at the first valid value:

Manual Entry (if user has explicitly set a value)
Invoice XML / Embedded Data
Supplier Catalog (uploaded file)
Supplier Product List (uploaded file)
Web Scraping Exception: Cost Price always comes from the latest approved invoice, but application requires user confirmation.
5.2 Poimenidis Code Normalization

Rule ID: NORM-POI-001 Rule: For Supplier "Ποιμενίδης", during parsing, if supplier_code starts with 03-, strip the prefix. The remaining string is the manufacturer_code. Example: 03-DCD996 → DCD996. Application: Applied during Step 5 (Normalization), before Step 6 (Matching).

5.3 Product Identity Independence

Rule ID: PROD-ID-001 Rule: The internal product identity is defined by the tuple (organization_id, name, manufacturer, base_barcode). It does NOT include pylon_code. Consequence: Two products with different pylon_codes but same barcode are the SAME product in Ergalyon. The pylon_code is merely an export attribute.

5.4 Soft Delete Behavior

Rule ID: DEL-SFT-001 Rule: When a supplier is soft-deleted (deleted_at is set):

It disappears from "Active Suppliers" lists.
It cannot be selected for new invoices.
Historical invoices linked to this supplier REMAIN visible and accessible.
The supplier can be restored by an ADMIN or OWNER. Rule ID: DEL-SFT-002 Rule: When a product is soft-deleted:
It disappears from active product lists.
Historical invoice items linked to it remain visible, showing the product name at the time of deletion.
The product_supplier_link is NOT deleted but marked as inactive.
5.5 Cost Price Overwrite Control

Rule ID: COST-OVR-001 Rule: The system NEVER automatically overwrites product_supplier_links.current_cost upon invoice parsing. Process:

Invoice is parsed and items matched.
System calculates "Suggested New Cost" for each matched product.
Dashboard shows "Pending Cost Updates".
User selects which updates to apply.
Only upon explicit user action (bulk or per-item) does the cost update.
Every update creates a row in product_cost_history.
5.6 Matching Confidence Thresholds

Rule ID: MAT-THR-001

Confidence >= 0.95: Auto-match. Status = MATCHED.
Confidence 0.70 - 0.94: Status = MANUAL_REVIEW. User must confirm.
Confidence < 0.70: Status = NEW_PRODUCT. User decides to create new or manually link.
5.7 Agreement RAG Scope Limitation

Rule ID: RAG-AGR-001 Rule: The RAG system indexing supplier agreements is ONLY for:

Semantic search ("Find the clause about returns in the Poimenidis agreement").
Chat interface (Q&A over agreement text). It MUST NOT be used to:
Validate invoice totals against agreement prices.
Auto-reject invoices.
Trigger alerts for non-compliance.
6. Technical Architecture
6.1 Infrastructure Layout

Hetzner Dedicated Server (Public Facing):

Docker Host: Ubuntu 22.04 LTS.
Services:
app: Next.js 14 (App Router) application.
db: PostgreSQL 16 (Business Data + Auth).
redis: Redis 7 (Queue for Crawl4AI, session cache).
nginx: Reverse proxy + SSL termination.
storage: MinIO or local mounted volume for PDF/XLSX storage.

Dell Laptop (Private AI Worker):

Location: Inside company network.
OS: Ubuntu 22.04.
Services:
ollama: Local LLM server (Llama 3.1 8B for chat, Llama 3.1 70B for analysis).
crawl4ai: Web scraping worker.
worker-queue: Consumes Redis jobs from Hetzner.
Connection: Secure tunnel (WireGuard or SSH reverse tunnel) to Hetzner. No public IP needed.
6.2 Database Strategy
Single Source of Truth: PostgreSQL on Hetzner.
Migration from v1: SQLite data from Ergalyon v1 will be exported and imported into PostgreSQL during deployment.
Backups: Daily pg_dump to Hetzner Storage Box.
