Tier 1 — Local (Dell Laptop):

Model: Llama 3.1 8B via Ollama.
Use: Chat interface, simple text normalization, supplier name detection.

Tier 2 — Local Heavy (Dell Laptop):

Model: Llama 3.1 70B via Ollama.
Use: Parser generation (JSON from invoice sample), complex table extraction.

Tier 3 — Cloud (Abacus AI):

Model: Claude Sonnet 3.5.
Use: Vision analysis of scanned invoices, fallback when local models fail, agreement RAG indexing.
Trigger: Automatic fallback if Tier 1/2 returns error or timeout (>30s).
6.4 Communication Flow
User uploads invoice to Hetzner app.
app stores file, creates DB record.
app attempts local parsing (hardcoded/dynamic).
If parsing needs AI:
Hetzner sends job to Redis queue (jobs:parsing).
Dell Laptop worker picks up job, processes with Ollama.
Worker posts result back to Hetzner API endpoint (/api/internal/ai-result).
If scraping needed:
Hetzner adds job to Redis queue (jobs:scraping).
Dell Laptop runs Crawl4AI, returns structured data.
