10. Migration Plan (v1 → v2)
Phase 0: Backup
Full snapshot of Ergalyon v1 SQLite database.
Zip of all uploaded PDFs and generated files.
Phase 1: Schema Migration
Run Prisma migration to create PostgreSQL schema on Hetzner.
Map SQLite tables to new PostgreSQL tables:
products → products + product_supplier_links
invoices → invoices + invoice_items
suppliers → suppliers + supplier_contacts
Phase 2: Data Migration Script
Python/Node script to read SQLite and write to PostgreSQL.
Handle data transformation (splitting old flat tables into normalized tables).
Generate initial product_supplier_links from old products table (where supplier code was embedded).
Phase 3: Parser Migration
Extract existing 12 hardcoded TypeScript parsers from v1.
Convert/adapt them to v2 structure (if needed) or keep them as-is in the parsers/ directory.
Phase 4: Cutover
Deploy v2 to Hetzner.
Run data migration.
Verify with Poimenidis test case.
Switch DNS/domain to v2.
